<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1210] IndexWriter &amp; ConcurrentMergeScheduler deadlock case if starting a merge hits an exception</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1210</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;If you&apos;re using CMS (the default) and mergeInit hits an exception (eg&lt;br/&gt;
OOME), we are not properly clearing IndexWriter&apos;s internal tracking of&lt;br/&gt;
running merges.  This causes IW.close() to hang while it incorrectly&lt;br/&gt;
waits for these non-started merges to finish.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
